### FlowChat API Testing
### Use with REST Client Extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@contentType = application/json

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/api/health

###

### Register New User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890",
  "password": "Test123456",
  "confirmPassword": "Test123456",
  "countryCode": "+1"
}

###

### Login User (with Email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "emailOrPhone": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123456"
}

###

### Login User (with Phone)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "emailOrPhone": "+1234567890",
  "password": "Test123456"
}

###

### Get Current User (Protected Route)
# Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN with the actual token from login response
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

###

### Update Password (Protected Route)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/auth/update-password
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "currentPassword": "Test123456",
  "newPassword": "NewPass123456",
  "confirmNewPassword": "NewPass123456"
}

###

### Check Username Availability
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/check-username/testuser

###

### Check Email Availability
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/check-email/test@example.com

###

### Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout

###

